

	 
       She picks up the edge of her dress  He slips his hand in hers  And so it starts   They begin to move  across the floor  Every move reflecting  grace and beauty  Some not perfect  But they don't care   It's no contest  There's no prize  They just enjoy  Gazing into the others' eyes   They slow down  and will soon stop  thislovely dance   They'll then part  Taking separate paths  But you and I know  they will always remember  The look in that one's eyes   The one that said  "This won't fade,  I shall always love you"  And so it ends...  this beautiful dance,  and off they go.   Not crying, yet not smiling.  And so it ends...   
    
